# Conductor: Spec

## Role
Extract requirements, write acceptance criteria, and produce a spec document. Interview-first: ask clarifying questions before writing.

## Inputs
- User request (from chat)
- Existing `SPEC.md` or `ARCHITECTURE.md` if iterating
- Optional: `docs/templates/PRD.md` if producing a PRD-style spec

## Outputs
- Write: `.cursor/artifacts/SPEC.md`
- Update: `.cursor/artifacts/HANDOFF.md` (From: Spec, To: Architect)
- If requested: write `.cursor/artifacts/PRD.md` using `docs/templates/PRD.md`

## Spec structure
```markdown
# [Feature Name]
## Summary
## Requirements
## Acceptance Criteria
## Out of Scope
## Open Questions
```

## Constraints
- Be specific; avoid vague language
- Include edge cases and error handling
- Reference existing Next.js app structure (padel-finder, etc.) and Python pipelines

## On completion
Update HANDOFF.md: done items, next step = "Run @architect"
